<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[813,1456,1300,1404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">DIAGNOSIS. — Small-sized shell, ovately conical, with up to 5 slightly convex whorls, the last large and elongate. Aperture pear-shaped, relatively high and elongate, adapically barely angulate, somewhat flared and slightly thickened inside. Umbilicus slit-like.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[813,1456,1460,2030]" box="[813,957,1460,1486]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[813,1456,1460,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
Shell small, solid, thick-walled, ovately conical, with up to 5 slightly convex whorls, the last large, elongate, exceeding two-thirds of shell height. Early whorls slowly increasing, the last faster and somewhat descending (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1342,1588,1615]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[132,143,1471,1489]" captionTargetBox="[146,1442,215,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[146,1442,214,1424]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — A, B, Hydrobia (s.l.) galatoniana n. sp., Galatone (Lecce, Apulia), Late Oligocene, paratype MPUR7-4198: A, apical view of the shell; B, detail of the protoconch; C, D, Hydrobia (s.l.) ionica n. sp., Galatone (Lecce, Apulia), Late Oligocene, paratype MPUR7-4199: C, apical view of the shell; D, detail of the protoconch. SEM image. Scale bars: A, C, 500 µm; B, D, 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678726/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Figs 2C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1353,1367,1589,1615]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="7.[132,143,1015,1033]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,970]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[132,1455,214,970]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIG. 4. — A-C, Hydrobia (s.l.) ionica n. sp.,Galatone (Lecce,Apulia),Late Oligocene:Aa-Ac, holotype MPUR7-3899;Ba-Bc, paratype MPUR7-4197/2a; Ca-Cc, paratype MPUR7-4197/2b. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678730/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">4</figureCitation>
Ab, Ba). Suture shallow, oblique between the penultimate and ultimate whorl. Protoconch of 
<emphasis box="[1115,1132,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1139,1226,1652,1679]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="410.0">410 µm</quantity>
maximum diameter, smooth, consisting of one slightly convex whorl. Boundary to teleoconch distinct by the formation of closely spaced growth lines (
<figureCitation box="[959,1045,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[132,143,1471,1489]" captionTargetBox="[146,1442,215,1424]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[146,1442,214,1424]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — A, B, Hydrobia (s.l.) galatoniana n. sp., Galatone (Lecce, Apulia), Late Oligocene, paratype MPUR7-4198: A, apical view of the shell; B, detail of the protoconch; C, D, Hydrobia (s.l.) ionica n. sp., Galatone (Lecce, Apulia), Late Oligocene, paratype MPUR7-4199: C, apical view of the shell; D, detail of the protoconch. SEM image. Scale bars: A, C, 500 µm; B, D, 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678726/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch glossy, with very delicate and thin prosocline growth lines. An axial swelling occurs sometimes in the last whorl towards the aperture. Aperture pear-shaped, high, elongate, adapically barely angulate and abapically rounded, somewhat flared and slightly thickened inside; peristome continuous, columellar lip almost completely adherent to the last whorl, outer lip straight in lateral profile. Umbilicus slit-like. Range dimensions: H = 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.0">4-4.5 mm</quantity>
, W = 
<quantity box="[927,1063,2003,2030]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5-2.7 mm</quantity>
, H/W = 1.48-1.8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[132,775,217,1105]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
Provisionally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Esu" box="[286,471,249,276]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Esu" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="183 - 195" refId="ref6499" refString="ESU D., GIROTTI O., IANNONE A., PIGNATTI J. S. &amp; RICCHETTI G. 1994. - Lagoonal-continental Oligocene of southern Apulia (Italy). Bollettino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana 33: 183 - 195." type="journal article" year="1994">
